<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 24 日星期三 14:37:25 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA['The Only Thing They Could Do': Why Ukraine Raided Russia's Belgorod Region]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110559580" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/18/1110561315_0:0:2157:1371_1440x900_80_0_1_e1646a02e5ff07ef3d4ff54c1d39369b.jpg?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1110561297" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/the-only-thing-they-could-do-why-ukraine-raided-russias-belgorod-region-1110559580.html?share-img=1110561297"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© 俄罗斯国防部新闻服务</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">乌克兰军队在对俄罗斯别尔哥罗德地区的不幸突袭中使用的被毁坏的军事装备</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="Wrecked military hardware used by Ukrainian troops in their ill-fated raid into Russia's Belgorod Region - Sputnik International, 1920, 24.05.2023" title="乌克兰军队在对俄罗斯别尔哥罗德地区的不幸突袭中使用的失事军事装备" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/18/1110561315_0:80:2157:1293_1920x0_80_0_0_f75696471ea7fa8c8cfb5d9f16365836.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/18/1110561315_0:80:2157:1293_640x0_80_0_0_dfbe2a4e7cf8cdc727f1960d73108f73.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/18/1110561315_0:80:2157:1293_1280x0_80_0_0_13e6a76ee9011b12844d7d93c4b2a4e6.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/18/1110561315_0:80:2157:1293_1920x0_80_0_0_f75696471ea7fa8c8cfb5d9f16365836.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 俄罗斯国防部新闻处</div>/ </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">安德烈·德加林</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_dergalin_andrei/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:a.dergalin@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">在阿尔乔莫夫斯克绞肉机中损失了数千名士兵并且仍未能守住这座城市之后，乌克兰军队显然试图通过对别尔哥罗德地区的平民发动出击来扳平比分。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>军事分析家瓦西里·丹迪金 (Vasily Dandykin)</strong>说，乌克兰军队<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/ukrainian-radicals-in-belgorod-region-blocked-eliminated---russian-mod-1110537418.html" target="_blank">注定要进军</a>俄罗斯的别尔哥罗德地区，这与基辅在阿尔捷莫夫斯克（巴赫穆特）遭受的军事灾难直接相关。<strong>俄罗斯海军一级上尉。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">经过数月的激烈战斗，俄罗斯军队于 5 月 21 日解放了阿尔捷莫夫斯克市，尽管乌克兰军队试图遵从泽连斯基总统的要求<strong>，不惜一切代价控制这座城市。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在接受人造卫星采访时，丹迪金指出，基辅损失了大约 50,000 名士兵，更多人受伤，并补充说乌克兰军队被驱逐出一个重要据点阿尔乔莫夫斯克，结果遭受了“道德失败”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “除了炮击顿巴斯领土外，这是他们所能做的（作为回应），”分析人士说，他指的是乌克兰的袭击。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110559580" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/the-only-thing-they-could-do-why-ukraine-raided-russias-belgorod-region-1110559580.html?share-block=1110560504" data-title="&quot;This is all they can do to [in response], aside from shelling the territory of Donbass,&quot; the analyst said, referring to the Ukrainian raid."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">丹迪金表示，基辅试图迫使莫斯科从前线调出部分军队，以保护受到乌克兰枪手行动威胁的俄罗斯领土，俄罗斯将拿出有效的反制措施来应对这种威胁。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他还驳斥了乌克兰方面关于别尔哥罗德地区的袭击不是乌克兰军队所为，而是由一些叛逃到乌克兰的俄罗斯“自发组织的志愿者”所为的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/medvedev-kievs-words-about-non-involvement-in-sabotage-attacks-in-russia-absolute-lie-1110539489.html" target="_blank">说法</a>。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “以前，我们曾[声称]自发组织的乌克兰爱国者，根据德国人和美国人的说法，他们炸毁了北溪 1 号和 2 号管道。这是同一种说法，”丹迪金评论道。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110559580" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/the-only-thing-they-could-do-why-ukraine-raided-russias-belgorod-region-1110559580.html?share-block=1110560506" data-title="&quot;Previously, we've had [claims about] the self-organized Ukrainian patriots who, according to the Germans and the Americans, blew up the Nord Stream 1 and 2 pipelines. This is the same kind of claim,&quot; Dandykin remarked."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，他确实注意到，乌克兰袭击别尔哥罗德地区的肇事者中有俄罗斯国民，他们曾于 3 月参与乌克兰对俄罗斯布良斯克地区两个村庄的袭击。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">他补充说：“这不是基辅当局第一次否认责任并将一切归咎于这些使用乌克兰武器和徽章并操作西方装甲车的‘自发组织’类型。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110559580" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/the-only-thing-they-could-do-why-ukraine-raided-russias-belgorod-region-1110559580.html?share-block=1110560507" data-title="&quot;This is not the first instance of the authorities in Kiev denying responsibility and blaming everything on these 'self-organized' types who sport Ukrainian weapons and insignia and operate Western armored vehicles,&quot; he added."></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 24 May 2023 14:03:52 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230524/the-only-thing-they-could-do-why-ukraine-raided-russias-belgorod-region-1110559580.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230524/the-only-thing-they-could-do-why-ukraine-raided-russias-belgorod-region-1110559580.html<category>俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别行动</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>别尔哥罗德州</category><category>攻击</category><category>目标</category><category>乌克兰进攻别尔哥罗德</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia Repels Ukraine's Drone Attacks on Ships Protecting Gas Pipelines in Turkiye]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110562484" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103151/41/1031514161_0:0:2464:1642_1440x900_80_0_1_9465e8a8e28fa136d82feb6ec3e0bffb.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1031514160" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/russia-repels-ukraines-drone-attacks-on-ships-protecting-gas-pipelines-in-turkiye-1110562484.html?share-img=1031514160"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / MUSTAFA OZER</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2005 年 11 月 16 日，一名工人走向土耳其北部萨姆松 Blue Stream 天然气管道的一个装置</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="A workers walks towards an installation at the Blue Stream gas pipeline in Samsun, northern Turkey, 16 November 2005 - Sputnik International, 1920, 24.05.2023" title="2005 年 11 月 16 日，一名工人走向土耳其北部萨姆松 Blue Stream 天然气管道的一个装置" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103151/41/1031514161_0:129:2464:1515_1920x0_80_0_0_3cc461d2735a5bf2cf53f4eec80a6d0d.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103151/41/1031514161_0:129:2464:1515_640x0_80_0_0_984fee8d3dafa9fcc4cfb535bcd65165.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103151/41/1031514161_0:129:2464:1515_1280x0_80_0_0_0475a016a12b795c9db3ca7fc1ca116e.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103151/41/1031514161_0:129:2464:1515_1920x0_80_0_0_3cc461d2735a5bf2cf53f4eec80a6d0d.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / MUSTAFA OZER </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__supplemented"><span class="point"></span>更新中</div><div class="article__announce-text">俄罗斯国防部周三表示，乌克兰试图用无人艇攻击俄罗斯黑海舰队“伊万库尔斯”号舰艇，但未成功，该舰确保了土耳其溪和蓝溪天然气管道的安全。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该部表示，俄罗斯军方在博斯普鲁斯海峡东北 140 公里（86.9 英里）处摧毁了所有敌方船只，并补充说 Ivan Khurs 号船继续履行其任务。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “ <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230403/hungarian-foreign-minister-slams-lack-of-nord-stream-investigation-as-insane-1109080682.html" target="_blank">在 2022 年 9 月 26 日对 Nord Stream-1 和 Nord Stream-2 的恐怖袭击</a>之后，俄罗斯军方一直在采取措施保护这些设施。而且没有白费。今天，凌晨 5:30 [当地时间，格林威治标准时间2:30]，乌克兰武装部队使用三艘无人驾驶高速艇试图攻击正在执行任务以确保土耳其溪和蓝溪天然气管道安全的Ivan Khurs号船，但没有成功。土耳其共和国的经济区，”该部说。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110562484" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/russia-repels-ukraines-drone-attacks-on-ships-protecting-gas-pipelines-in-turkiye-1110562484.html?share-block=1110562934" data-title="&amp;quot;After the terrorist attack on September 26, 2022 on the Nord Stream-1 and Nord Stream-2, the Russian military has been taking measures to protect such facilities. And not in vain. Today, at 5:30 a.m. [local time, 2:30 GMT], the Ukrainian armed forces with the use of three unmanned high-speed boats made an unsuccessful attempt to attack the ship Ivan Khurs that was performing tasks to ensure the safety of the Turkish Stream and Blue Stream gas pipelines in the exclusive economic zone of the Republic of Turkiye,&amp;quot; the ministry said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">蓝溪是从俄罗斯通过黑海向土耳其输送天然气的主要天然气管道。这条由俄罗斯天然气工业股份公司和意大利能源公司建造的管道贯穿东欧地区。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> TurkStream（前身为 Turkish Stream）是一条耗资 115 亿欧元的管道，每年能够向 Turkiye 输送高达 315 亿立方米的 Russianb 天然气。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 24 May 2023 14:02:48 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230524/russia-repels-ukraines-drone-attacks-on-ships-protecting-gas-pipelines-in-turkiye-1110562484.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230524/russia-repels-ukraines-drone-attacks-on-ships-protecting-gas-pipelines-in-turkiye-1110562484.html<category>俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别行动</category><category>乌克兰危机</category><category>军队</category><category>蓝溪天然气管道</category><category>土耳其流管道</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Washington Politicians Won't Risk 'Cataclysmic' Default Over Debt Ceiling Crisis]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110555898" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0b/1d/1091122895_0:0:3295:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_14eab6e00725ba40a4d7bfad357e5920.jpg?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1091122891" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/washington-politicians-wont-risk-cataclysmic-default-over-debt-ceiling-crisis-1110555898.html?share-img=1091122891"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Chris Wattie</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2018 年 8 月 22 日摄于美国华盛顿特区的美联储大楼。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="The Federal Reserve building is pictured in Washington, D.C., U.S., August 22, 2018. - Sputnik International, 1920, 24.05.2023" title="美联储大楼于 2018 年 8 月 22 日在美国华盛顿特区拍摄。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0b/1d/1091122895_0:0:3295:1853_1920x0_80_0_0_32fd162debfeef26ea1fdc8d873910c7.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0b/1d/1091122895_0:0:3295:1853_640x0_80_0_0_2ff98f8c597fdd5a131fa041d96dc64c.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0b/1d/1091122895_0:0:3295:1853_1280x0_80_0_0_d386603c26ea06a7e16398de690070c3.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0b/1d/1091122895_0:0:3295:1853_1920x0_80_0_0_32fd162debfeef26ea1fdc8d873910c7.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 克里斯·瓦蒂</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-image"><img media-type="s150x150" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="James Tweedie - Sputnik International" title="詹姆斯·特威迪" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1c/1080307270_0:3:397:400_100x100_80_0_0_7777393b9b18802f2e3c5eaa9cbcc612.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">詹姆斯·特威迪</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_tweedie_james/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:j.tweedie@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">经济学家、教授兼顾问马克·弗罗斯特 (Mark Frost) 警告说，让美国财政部拖欠债务将带来灾难性的后果——但这就是为什么美国人不应该担心政治对手会让它碰巧互相怨恨。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">一位经济学家表示，由于担心削弱美元，共和党和民主党将不可避免地就提高债务上限达成协议。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">随着财政部长珍妮特耶伦设定的 6 月 1 日取消政府借款上限的最后期限迅速临近，民主党总统乔拜登和共和党众议院议长凯文麦卡锡在周一的第三次会议后未能达成协议。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">耶伦警告说，如果国会不批准将借款限额从 1.1 万亿美元提高到 1.5 万亿美元，政府将无力支付账单——可能包括<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/us-treasury-reportedly-asks-if-federal-agencies-can-delay-payments-to-avert-debt-default-1110546437.html" target="_blank">国家雇员的工资</a>和福利金。作为回报，共和党人要求削减公共开支。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">但<strong>马克弗罗斯特</strong>告诉<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/rfk-jr-attacks-donald-trumps-2020-lockdowns-and-weaponization-of-the-fbi-1110549130.html" target="_blank">人造卫星</a>，主流媒体对债务上限僵局和联邦违约风险的报道“只是夸张”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “首先，不会有任何违约，”他坚持说。 “我不在乎那些人在过道对面有多恨对方。每一方都知道焦土不是他们想要的。这就是现在的情况。” </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “他们可能会让政府关门。他们可能会演各种小戏。但唯一重要的是债务利息是否支付，”弗罗斯特说。 “如果没有支付，如果它被推迟，无论什么没有支付。这就是违约。债务的利息在到期时没有支付。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110555898" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/washington-politicians-wont-risk-cataclysmic-default-over-debt-ceiling-crisis-1110555898.html?share-block=1110559219" data-title="&quot;They might do a government shutdown. They might do all kinds of little dramas. But the only thing that matters in this is whether the interest on the debt is paid or it's not paid,&quot; Frost said. &quot;If it's not paid, if it's postponed, whatever that's not being paid. That's a default. The interest on the debt is not paid when it's due.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位经济学家说，民主党人和共和党人都不会冒这样的后果。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">弗罗斯特警告说：“国债的利息将得到支付，因为双方都知道，让它违约的灾难性反乌托邦后果高得令人望而却步。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110555898" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/washington-politicians-wont-risk-cataclysmic-default-over-debt-ceiling-crisis-1110555898.html?share-block=1110560944" data-title="&quot;The interest on the national debt is going to get paid because the cost, the cataclysmic dystopian consequences of letting it default, both sides know, is just prohibitively high,&quot; Frost warned."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">债务违约的一个主要后果是人们对美元作为国际储备和贸易货币的信心丧失——随着俄罗斯、中国、印度和其他国家转向以自己的面额结算付款，这已经成为问题。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “美元成为记账单位和储备货币的原因，以及美国以外对美元的需求占 60% 至 70% 的原因，正是因为我们从未支付过债务利息”弗罗斯特解释道。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110555898" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/washington-politicians-wont-risk-cataclysmic-default-over-debt-ceiling-crisis-1110555898.html?share-block=1110559220" data-title="&quot;The reason the dollar is the unit of account and the reserve currency, and the reason that the demand for US dollars is 60 to 70 per cent represented outside the United States, is precisely because we've never not paid the interest on the debt,&quot; Frost explained."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “最终，在第 11 个小时，双方将聚在一起，”并达成协议，这位学者预测道。 “而且每一方都将赢得胜利。” </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">弗罗斯特强调说：“作为一个数学家，我从来不使用零概率或 100% 概率这个词，但他们拖欠债务的概率是彩票赔率类型的数学。我的意思是，它是只是不会发生。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110555898" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/washington-politicians-wont-risk-cataclysmic-default-over-debt-ceiling-crisis-1110555898.html?share-block=1110559221" data-title="&quot;Being a math guy, I don't ever use the word zero probability or 100 percent probability,&quot; Frost stressed, &quot;But the probability that they're going to default on the debt is lottery odds-type math. I mean, it's just not going to happen.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>如需对最新新闻报道进行更深入的分析，请查看我们的 Sputnik 广播节目<em><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/radio-the-backstory/" target="_blank">The Backstory。</a></em></strong></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 24 May 2023 13:37:31 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230524/washington-politicians-wont-risk-cataclysmic-default-over-debt-ceiling-crisis-1110555898.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230524/washington-politicians-wont-risk-cataclysmic-default-over-debt-ceiling-crisis-1110555898.html<category>美洲</category><category>我们</category><category>债务</category><category>美国债务上限危机</category><category>珍妮特·耶伦</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>华盛顿</category><category>共和党人</category><category>民主党人</category><category>金库</category><category>凯文麦卡锡</category></item></channel></rss>